WEBVTT

1
00:01:38.840 --> 00:01:40.295
How is everything.
Mr. Sabian?

2
00:01:40.320 --> 00:01:41.815
Great. as always.
Good.

3
00:01:41.840 --> 00:01:43.922
You get home now. Eva.
It's getting late.

4
00:01:44.440 --> 00:01:46.135
Stay safe.

5
00:01:46.160 --> 00:01:48.615
Yeah. You. too.
Mr. Sabian.

6
00:01:48.640 --> 00:01:50.455
<i>Traffic is
building rapidly downtown.</i>

7
00:01:50.480 --> 00:01:53.375
<i>as citizens rush to get home
before commencement.</i>

8
00:01:53.400 --> 00:01:55.335
<i>If you're not Purging.
we advise you</i>

9
00:01:55.360 --> 00:01:57.175
<i>to get off the streets
as quickly as possible.</i>

10
00:01:57.200 --> 00:01:58.929
<i>It'll soon be a war out there.</i>

11
00:01:59.160 --> 00:02:01.255
<i>Prognosticators estimate
that more people</i>

12
00:02:01.280 --> 00:02:02.361
<i>will partake in
this year's Purge...</i>

13
00:02:02.520 --> 00:02:04.284
Sabian's gone.
That's it.

14
00:02:04.440 --> 00:02:06.568
What is she waiting for? Why
doesn't this bitch let us go?

15
00:02:06.720 --> 00:02:09.215
Hey. calm down.
We got plenty of time.

16
00:02:09.240 --> 00:02:11.083
You girls up to
anything fun tonight?

17
00:02:11.200 --> 00:02:13.202
I might kidnap Eva this year.

18
00:02:13.400 --> 00:02:14.970
Hope that's okay with you. <i>mami.</i>

19
00:02:16.880 --> 00:02:18.245
It's getting late.

20
00:02:18.400 --> 00:02:20.880
Hope to see you all tomorrow.
Stay safe.

21
00:02:21.040 --> 00:02:22.215
Okay. stay safe.

22
00:02:22.240 --> 00:02:25.323
Finally.
Stay safe. Mrs. Crawley.

23
00:02:30.720 --> 00:02:32.655
Eva.

24
00:02:32.680 --> 00:02:34.170
Need a ride home?

25
00:02:34.320 --> 00:02:35.845
I'm fine. Carlos.

26
00:02:36.000 --> 00:02:40.215
Stay safe.

27
00:02:40.240 --> 00:02:42.402
Bye. Carlito.
Stay safe.

28
00:02:44.040 --> 00:02:46.895
If he asked to take me home.
I'd accept that ride. girl.

29
00:02:46.920 --> 00:02:48.046
He's a dog.

30
00:02:48.400 --> 00:02:51.244
I like that dog. I would
walk the shit out of that dog.

31
00:02:51.440 --> 00:02:53.360
But that dog doesn't want
anything to do with me.

32
00:02:53.400 --> 00:02:54.735
he wants to sniff your ass.

33
00:02:54.760 --> 00:02:55.895
You're disgusting.

34
00:02:55.920 --> 00:02:57.285
It's true.

35
00:02:59.000 --> 00:03:00.923
You're really gonna
ask her tonight?

36
00:03:01.240 --> 00:03:02.685
I have to.

37
00:03:02.840 --> 00:03:05.286
I can't afford his
medicine much longer.

38
00:03:06.720 --> 00:03:08.768
All right. good luck.

39
00:03:10.000 --> 00:03:11.126
Stay safe.

40
00:03:12.400 --> 00:03:13.970
Stay safe. sweetie.

41
00:03:18.400 --> 00:03:19.811
Okay.

42
00:04:10.040 --> 00:04:12.735
<i>Both the people and
the government wanted the Purge.</i>

43
00:04:12.760 --> 00:04:14.655
<i>The New Founding
Fathers came into office...</i>

44
00:04:14.680 --> 00:04:17.055
<i>Were voted into office
by a country who wanted change...</i>

45
00:04:17.080 --> 00:04:19.895
<i>This new regime took
advantage of the nation's fear.</i>

46
00:04:28.600 --> 00:04:30.815
I'm glad we took the back roads.

47
00:04:30.840 --> 00:04:33.810
The highways are probably
a mess right now.

48
00:04:34.280 --> 00:04:36.965
Yeah.
We'll be there in no time.

49
00:04:37.120 --> 00:04:38.326
Yeah.

50
00:04:48.120 --> 00:04:49.246
What are you looking at?

51
00:04:51.320 --> 00:04:54.210
Nothing.
Just. you know. stuff.

52
00:04:59.360 --> 00:05:00.646
Are you okay?

53
00:05:01.880 --> 00:05:04.486
Yeah. I'm fine.

54
00:05:06.200 --> 00:05:07.770
You sure?

55
00:05:08.200 --> 00:05:10.248
You don't need
to keep asking me.

56
00:05:17.560 --> 00:05:19.695
<i>My name is Donald Talbot.</i>

57
00:05:19.720 --> 00:05:23.055
<i>Our regime was voted into
office nine years ago.</i>

58
00:05:23.080 --> 00:05:24.855
<i>And the first order of business</i>

59
00:05:24.880 --> 00:05:27.015
<i>was to deal with
the epidemic of crime</i>

60
00:05:27.040 --> 00:05:28.883
<i>that was plaguing this nation.</i>

61
00:05:29.120 --> 00:05:32.010
<i>The answer was the Purge.</i>

62
00:05:37.040 --> 00:05:38.815
You need some protection tonight?
You need something?

63
00:05:38.840 --> 00:05:40.175
Hey. man. we running out of...

64
00:05:40.200 --> 00:05:41.895
Hey. that Purge tonight.
y'all know what time it is.

65
00:05:41.920 --> 00:05:43.615
Hitting them in the face
ain't gonna work no more.

66
00:05:43.640 --> 00:05:45.051
You need something powerful.

67
00:05:45.920 --> 00:05:47.055
How you doing. buddy?

68
00:05:47.080 --> 00:05:49.735
Use your hands. man. Just use your hands.
Don't even worry about it.

69
00:05:49.760 --> 00:05:51.375
Hey. sweetheart. how you doing?
How you doing?

70
00:05:51.400 --> 00:05:52.481
You gonna need something
for protection tonight?

71
00:05:52.600 --> 00:05:54.095
No. No. I'm good. I'm good.
UZI? Beretta?

72
00:05:54.120 --> 00:05:55.690
Look. on the cheap-cheap.

73
00:05:55.800 --> 00:05:58.201
Or a blade to cut your man's throat?
Whatever you need.

74
00:05:58.680 --> 00:06:00.762
We take any kind of payment.

75
00:06:09.440 --> 00:06:10.441
Eva!

76
00:06:10.560 --> 00:06:12.483
Hey. Diego. What's up. girl?
How you doing?

77
00:06:12.600 --> 00:06:14.250
Good. How you doing?
Yeah? Everything's great?

78
00:06:14.400 --> 00:06:15.695
No. it's not great.
I'm tired...

79
00:06:15.720 --> 00:06:16.895
It could be better.

80
00:06:16.920 --> 00:06:18.695
Take me up there with you tonight.
Get a little protection.

81
00:06:18.720 --> 00:06:19.720
You know what I'm saying?

82
00:06:19.800 --> 00:06:20.935
Come on. now. I'm cool. Diego.
I'm good.

83
00:06:20.960 --> 00:06:22.015
You sure you don't
want no protection?

84
00:06:22.040 --> 00:06:23.095
No. thanks. Diego.

85
00:06:23.120 --> 00:06:24.935
I'm the man for the job.
You know what I mean?

86
00:06:24.960 --> 00:06:28.646
<i>We've lost our
souls to attain this peace.</i>

87
00:06:29.480 --> 00:06:32.324
<i>We no longer worship
at the altar of Christ.</i>

88
00:06:32.600 --> 00:06:35.490
<i>Muhammad. Yahweh.</i>

89
00:06:35.640 --> 00:06:39.295
<i>We worship at the altar
of Smith & Wesson.</i>

90
00:06:39.320 --> 00:06:42.324
<i>We. the people.
know not what we do.</i>

91
00:06:42.480 --> 00:06:45.689
Horseshit. Where'd
you find this lunatic?

92
00:06:45.800 --> 00:06:47.564
I saw his protest posters
all around the neighborhood.

93
00:06:47.760 --> 00:06:49.375
He lives here. Papa.
He's just like us.

94
00:06:49.400 --> 00:06:52.815
Now. shush. Please listen. He's
not a lunatic.

95
00:06:52.840 --> 00:06:55.295
<i>The Purge is not about
containing crime to one night.</i>

96
00:06:55.320 --> 00:06:58.375
<i>and cleansing our souls
by releasing aggression.</i>

97
00:06:58.400 --> 00:07:01.529
<i>It's about one thing.
Money.</i>

98
00:07:02.320 --> 00:07:05.961
<i>Who dies tonight? The poor.</i>

99
00:07:06.480 --> 00:07:09.165
<i>We can't afford to
protect ourselves.</i>

100
00:07:09.360 --> 00:07:11.089
That's enough.
I can't listen to this crap.

101
00:07:11.200 --> 00:07:12.480
He's as full of shit
as they are.

102
00:07:12.520 --> 00:07:15.255
No. he's right. Come on. They're
keeping the population down

103
00:07:15.280 --> 00:07:17.521
by getting rid of people
like us to save money.

104
00:07:17.680 --> 00:07:19.815
Talk is cheap. Cali.

105
00:07:19.840 --> 00:07:22.320
He may be right. but he
won't do anything about it.

106
00:07:22.760 --> 00:07:24.444
Home.

107
00:07:29.680 --> 00:07:30.727
Hey. Daddy.

108
00:07:30.840 --> 00:07:33.415
Don't "hey. Daddy" me.
Where have you been?

109
00:07:33.440 --> 00:07:35.249
We're less than two hours
until commencement.

110
00:07:35.360 --> 00:07:36.695
and you're out gallivanting.

111
00:07:36.720 --> 00:07:38.210
Gallivanting? I was
picking up your medicine.

112
00:07:38.360 --> 00:07:41.364
Even worse.
A waste of time and money.

113
00:07:41.560 --> 00:07:43.735
Christ. Eva. I told you
not to get this stuff.

114
00:07:43.760 --> 00:07:45.415
I'm tired of listening
to this every day.

115
00:07:45.440 --> 00:07:46.771
It does nothing...
I'm not taking it!

116
00:07:46.880 --> 00:07:48.775
You're taking your medicine. I'm
not taking it! No. I'm not!

117
00:07:48.800 --> 00:07:51.095
Yes. you are! I'm not taking it.
You're taking it back.

118
00:07:51.120 --> 00:07:52.735
My God. really?

119
00:07:52.760 --> 00:07:53.761
Can we stop?

120
00:07:56.680 --> 00:08:00.082
Look. Papa. maybe it doesn't do
anything. but can you just take it?

121
00:08:00.520 --> 00:08:02.090
For me?

122
00:08:06.720 --> 00:08:08.085
Okay.

123
00:08:08.240 --> 00:08:11.642
We'll lockdown and then
we'll eat after commencement.

124
00:08:11.760 --> 00:08:12.886
Count me out.

125
00:08:13.760 --> 00:08:16.684
I'm gonna take a long nap.
and don't bother me.

126
00:08:17.160 --> 00:08:20.243
I'm gonna try to sleep through
this godforsaken holiday.

127
00:08:24.040 --> 00:08:27.761
Look. I'm sorry
I'm so grumpy. girls.

128
00:08:28.360 --> 00:08:30.567
I hate this night.

129
00:08:31.000 --> 00:08:33.765
Please. forgive me.

130
00:08:39.120 --> 00:08:41.487
You drive me crazy.

131
00:08:47.440 --> 00:08:49.681
Make sure you
lockdown everything.

132
00:08:51.080 --> 00:08:53.287
I'll take care of my room.

133
00:08:55.040 --> 00:08:56.724
I love you both.

134
00:08:57.440 --> 00:08:59.124
Very much.

135
00:09:01.120 --> 00:09:02.645
I know.

136
00:09:10.240 --> 00:09:12.129
That was weird.

137
00:09:12.320 --> 00:09:13.970
It must be the night.

138
00:09:15.080 --> 00:09:16.241
Yeah.

139
00:09:17.640 --> 00:09:20.120
I'm gonna take a quick shower.
and then we'll lockdown.

140
00:09:20.280 --> 00:09:23.090
Okay. wait. How did things go with Mrs.
Crawley?

141
00:09:23.600 --> 00:09:25.489
Did you get the raise?

142
00:09:27.960 --> 00:09:30.008
God. what a bitch.

143
00:09:30.160 --> 00:09:31.535
Well. did you at least
make a good argument?

144
00:09:31.560 --> 00:09:34.086
Did you say everything
that we practiced?

145
00:09:36.680 --> 00:09:38.330
I'm sorry. baby.

146
00:09:40.160 --> 00:09:41.605
Yeah.

147
00:09:57.360 --> 00:09:59.249
I want to tell her. Shane.

148
00:10:07.040 --> 00:10:09.361
Hey. did you hear me?

149
00:10:09.680 --> 00:10:11.135
I said I wanna tell
your sister...

150
00:10:11.160 --> 00:10:12.575
Yeah. I heard you.

151
00:10:12.600 --> 00:10:15.649
I just don't feel
like telling her.

152
00:10:16.280 --> 00:10:17.520
Why?

153
00:10:19.360 --> 00:10:22.284
Because as soon as you say it
out loud to another person.

154
00:10:23.120 --> 00:10:24.963
then it's irreversible.

155
00:10:26.960 --> 00:10:28.962
Do you have the keys?

156
00:10:29.120 --> 00:10:30.326
Yeah.

157
00:10:30.560 --> 00:10:31.846
Handy?

158
00:10:32.200 --> 00:10:33.326
Right here.

159
00:10:34.200 --> 00:10:35.535
Can you unlock the car. please?

160
00:10:35.560 --> 00:10:36.721
It's unlocked.

161
00:10:37.120 --> 00:10:38.360
No. it's not.

162
00:10:38.720 --> 00:10:39.881
There.

163
00:11:31.240 --> 00:11:32.765
Let's just get in the car.

164
00:11:37.120 --> 00:11:38.485
What the fuck
was that all about?

165
00:11:38.640 --> 00:11:40.815
I don't know.
He didn't tell me.

166
00:11:40.840 --> 00:11:43.255
You know. we don't have a whole lot
of time before commencement. Shane.

167
00:11:43.280 --> 00:11:46.409
All right.
We'll be fine. I promise.

168
00:12:02.800 --> 00:12:03.801
Yeah.

169
00:12:06.800 --> 00:12:08.643
I've been calling.
Why didn't you pick up?

170
00:12:10.160 --> 00:12:11.650
What do you want?

171
00:12:20.520 --> 00:12:22.615
You can't go out there. You
know how dangerous it is...

172
00:12:22.640 --> 00:12:24.165
You need to go.
You need to leave.

173
00:12:26.440 --> 00:12:28.010
It's late.

174
00:12:29.560 --> 00:12:31.403
Don't do this.

175
00:12:33.160 --> 00:12:35.925
It won't make you
feel any better.

176
00:12:38.240 --> 00:12:40.163
Go with your new husband.

177
00:12:40.840 --> 00:12:43.127
and your new family.

178
00:12:44.560 --> 00:12:46.164
Leave.

179
00:12:53.560 --> 00:12:55.324
Just stay safe.

180
00:13:06.520 --> 00:13:08.124
You. too.

181
00:13:22.040 --> 00:13:24.407
<i>Whatever happened
to "Give me your needy."</i>

182
00:13:25.600 --> 00:13:27.855
<i>"your tired."</i>

183
00:13:27.880 --> 00:13:32.169
<i>"your huddled masses
yearning to breathe free"?</i>

184
00:13:32.880 --> 00:13:35.655
<i>The redistribution
of wealth upward</i>

185
00:13:35.680 --> 00:13:37.569
<i>through killing has to stop.</i>

186
00:13:38.680 --> 00:13:40.489
<i>We must pick up arms.</i>

187
00:13:42.720 --> 00:13:45.564
<i>This year. we will fight back!</i>

188
00:14:37.280 --> 00:14:39.487
Jeez. that guy freaked me out.

189
00:14:39.800 --> 00:14:41.802
Did not see him coming.

190
00:14:41.960 --> 00:14:44.770
I thought we decided
it was irreversible.

191
00:14:47.240 --> 00:14:49.895
No. you often decide
things on your own.

192
00:14:49.920 --> 00:14:52.048
and then pretend that they
were a joint decision.

193
00:14:52.160 --> 00:14:53.575
You often agree with me.

194
00:14:53.600 --> 00:14:54.775
and then a week later say.

195
00:14:54.800 --> 00:14:56.320
"I don't remember
doing that."

196
00:14:56.400 --> 00:14:57.640
So. you're calling me a liar?

197
00:14:57.800 --> 00:14:59.723
And you're calling me a bully.

198
00:15:00.280 --> 00:15:02.015
Just say you changed your mind.

199
00:15:02.040 --> 00:15:04.486
not that we didn't come
to a joint decision.

200
00:15:05.320 --> 00:15:07.004
This is the exact...

201
00:15:14.680 --> 00:15:17.815
See. this is exactly why we
need to tell your sister

202
00:15:17.840 --> 00:15:19.251
that we're separating.

203
00:15:19.760 --> 00:15:21.815
You're right.
it'll make it real.

204
00:15:21.840 --> 00:15:24.002
but I think we need
to make it real.

205
00:15:24.160 --> 00:15:26.401
Maybe I don't wanna
make it real.

206
00:15:30.480 --> 00:15:32.080
Whoa. whoa. whoa.

207
00:15:32.360 --> 00:15:33.575
What the hell is that?

208
00:15:33.600 --> 00:15:34.815
The power steering's gone.

209
00:15:34.840 --> 00:15:36.335
What do you mean
"the power steering's gone"?

210
00:15:36.360 --> 00:15:38.169
I don't know. There's
something wrong with the car.

211
00:15:38.320 --> 00:15:40.322
Can you pull over?
I'm trying.

212
00:15:50.760 --> 00:15:51.935
Shit.

213
00:15:51.960 --> 00:15:53.405
Try it again.

214
00:15:58.280 --> 00:15:59.930
It's dead.

215
00:16:23.200 --> 00:16:26.966
<i>The sixth Annual
Purge will begin in 45 minutes.</i>

216
00:16:45.720 --> 00:16:46.801
Just in case.

217
00:16:46.960 --> 00:16:48.007
Yeah.

218
00:16:51.360 --> 00:16:52.441
Hey.

219
00:16:53.320 --> 00:16:55.049
We're gonna be fine.

220
00:16:55.640 --> 00:16:57.404
Just like every year.

221
00:16:58.680 --> 00:17:00.091
Yeah.

222
00:17:01.960 --> 00:17:03.962
I'll pay three times as much
if you just come out here...

223
00:17:04.120 --> 00:17:06.455
No. no. no. I don't care about the car.
We just need a ride.

224
00:17:06.480 --> 00:17:07.680
It's... Hello?
Whoa. whoa! Hey!

225
00:17:08.680 --> 00:17:10.569
Hey! Whoa. whoa. whoa!

226
00:17:13.280 --> 00:17:14.964
Stop!
Shit.

227
00:17:15.120 --> 00:17:16.485
Please!

228
00:17:18.960 --> 00:17:21.440
Shane. we can't be stuck outside.
I know. I know.

229
00:17:21.640 --> 00:17:24.041
We're downtown. Everyone
comes downtown to Purge.

230
00:17:24.200 --> 00:17:25.770
Hey. hey.
Don't worry.

231
00:17:25.920 --> 00:17:28.455
We'll figure something
out. I promise.

232
00:17:31.000 --> 00:17:33.082
Is that coming from our car?

233
00:17:37.520 --> 00:17:39.124
Shit.

234
00:18:12.160 --> 00:18:14.335
He cut those wires. Shane.

235
00:18:14.360 --> 00:18:15.407
Yeah.

236
00:18:22.240 --> 00:18:23.695
We need to run.

237
00:18:23.720 --> 00:18:24.721
Yeah. go. go.

238
00:18:35.240 --> 00:18:37.055
<i>News 13 wishes anyone</i>

239
00:18:37.080 --> 00:18:40.455
<i>who is not participating in this
year's Purge a safe evening</i>

240
00:18:40.480 --> 00:18:44.015
<i>and for those releasing the
beast. a successful cleanse.</i>

241
00:18:44.040 --> 00:18:45.135
<i>Good luck.</i>

242
00:18:45.160 --> 00:18:46.605
Should I get Papa?

243
00:18:47.080 --> 00:18:49.003
He hates this.
Let him sleep.

244
00:18:49.160 --> 00:18:50.650
<i>This is not a test.</i>

245
00:18:50.880 --> 00:18:53.281
<i>This is your Emergency
Broadcast System</i>

246
00:18:53.400 --> 00:18:55.655
<i>announcing the commencement
of The Annual Purge</i>

247
00:18:55.680 --> 00:18:58.081
<i>sanctioned by the US Government.</i>

248
00:18:58.920 --> 00:19:00.855
<i>Weapons of Class 4 and lower</i>

249
00:19:00.880 --> 00:19:03.611
<i>have been authorized
for use during the Purge.</i>

250
00:19:03.760 --> 00:19:05.762
<i>All other weapons
are restricted.</i>

251
00:19:05.920 --> 00:19:09.402
<i>Government officials of ranking
10 have been granted immunity...</i>

252
00:19:13.160 --> 00:19:17.290
<i>Commencing at the siren. any and
